{"repo": "frappe/bench", "pull_number": 1632, "instance_id": "frappe__bench-1632", "issue_numbers": [1633], "base_commit": "f01f10510667464ad333ff41e0644c88a0ca5fa4", "patch": "diff --git a/.github/workflows/ci.yml b/.github/workflows/ci.yml\nindex a5b4ed78d..2b86f30d5 100644\n--- a/.github/workflows/ci.yml\n+++ b/.github/workflows/ci.yml\n@@ -21,7 +21,7 @@ jobs:\n     strategy:\n       fail-fast: false\n       matrix:\n-        python-version: ['3.9', '3.10', '3.11', '3.12', '3.13']\n+        python-version: ['3.10', '3.11', '3.12', '3.13']\n \n     name: Base (${{ matrix.python-version }})\n \ndiff --git a/bench/utils/cli.py b/bench/utils/cli.py\nindex 6cae95f6f..a805305cb 100644\n--- a/bench/utils/cli.py\n+++ b/bench/utils/cli.py\n@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@\n from typing import List\n import click\n-from click.core import _check_multicommand\n+from click.core import _check_nested_chain\n \n \n def print_bench_version(ctx, param, value):\n@@ -25,7 +25,7 @@ def add_command(self, cmd, name=None):\n \t\tname = name or cmd.name\n \t\tif name is None:\n \t\t\traise TypeError(\"Command has no name.\")\n-\t\t_check_multicommand(self, name, cmd, register=True)\n+\t\t_check_nested_chain(self, name, cmd, register=True)\n \n \t\ttry:\n \t\t\tself.commands[name] = cmd\ndiff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml\nindex 610ee1c3d..0c86823f3 100644\n--- a/pyproject.toml\n+++ b/pyproject.toml\n@@ -19,7 +19,7 @@ classifiers = [\n     \"Topic :: System :: Installation/Setup\",\n ]\n dependencies = [\n-    \"Click>=7.0\",\n+    \"Click~=8.2.0\",\n     \"GitPython~=3.1.30\",\n     \"honcho\",\n     \"Jinja2~=3.1.3\",\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Strict Click Versions\nWe need to have a strict `Click` version since a major version update fails to resolve:\n\n`from click.core import _check_multicommand_`\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Same here, frappe_docker build is failing because of this:\n```\n > [builder 3/3] RUN export APP_INSTALL_ARGS=\"\" &&   if [ -n \"Ww0KICAgIHsNCiAgICAgICJ1cmwiOiAiaHR0cHM6Ly9naXRodWIuY29tL2ZyYXBwZS9lcnBuZXh0IiwNCiAgICAgICJicmFuY2giOiAidmVyc2lvbi0xNSINCiAgICB9LA0KICAgIHsNCiAgICAgICJ1cmwiOiAiaHR0cHM6Ly9naXRodWIuY29tL2ZyYXBwZS9wYXltZW50cyIsDQogICAgICAiYnJhbmNoIjogInZlcnNpb24tMTUiDQogICAgfQ0KICBd\" ]; then     export APP_INSTALL_ARGS=\"--apps_path=/opt/frappe/apps.json\";   fi &&   bench init ${APP_INSTALL_ARGS}    --frappe-branch=version-15     --frappe-path=https://github.com/frappe/frappe     --no-procfile     --no-backups     --skip-redis-config-generation     --verbose     /home/frappe/frappe-bench &&   cd /home/frappe/frappe-bench &&   echo \"{}\" > sites/common_site_config.json &&   find apps -mindepth 1 -path \"*/.git\" | xargs rm -fr:\n\n2.078 Traceback (most recent call last):\n2.078   File \"/usr/local/bin/bench\", line 5, in <module>\n2.078     from bench.cli import cli\n2.078   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages/bench/cli.py\", line 15, in <module>\n2.078     from bench.commands import bench_command\n2.078   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages/bench/commands/__init__.py\", line 5, in <module>\n2.078     from bench.utils.cli import (\n2.078   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages/bench/utils/cli.py\", line 3, in <module>\n2.078     from click.core import _check_multicommand\n2.078 ImportError: cannot import name '_check_multicommand' from 'click.core' (/usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages/click/core.py)\n```\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/frappe/bench/commit/a8ed8e1cf144f9dfda64d62caf08c6fc0c338c3a", "https://github.com/frappe/bench/commit/a2cd719af4a4a0cebd8c2565b37b85d48a1f6591", "https://github.com/frappe/bench/commit/408ebbf9725bec91ed02315e6bdf7f6a82474116"], "created_at": "2025-05-11T08:34:58Z"}
{"repo": "frappe/bench", "pull_number": 1699, "instance_id": "frappe__bench-1699", "issue_numbers": [1698], "base_commit": "5107f1df45eb5f780a54073d027cab7442a39b46", "patch": "diff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml\nindex b20e9e457..c4a9ee21c 100644\n--- a/pyproject.toml\n+++ b/pyproject.toml\n@@ -26,7 +26,7 @@ dependencies = [\n     \"python-crontab~=2.6.0\",\n     \"requests~=2.32.5\",\n     \"semantic-version~=2.10.0\",\n-    \"setuptools>=71.0.0\",\n+    \"setuptools>=71.0.0,<82.0.0\",\n     \"tomli;python_version<'3.11'\",\n     \"uv~=0.9.0 \"\n ]\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Setuptools v82.0.0 breaking compatibility with frappe v15\nIssue: The recent released `setuptools` v82.0.0 doesn't contain `pkg_resources` any longer, which dropbox  (frappe v15 dependency) depends on. Due to this, bench new-site will always fail due to the missing dependency.\n\n**Do the checklist before filing an issue:**\n - [X] Can you replicate the issue on the supported bench versions?\n\n**To Reproduce** :page_with_curl:\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n1. Setup new docker bench development container\n2. Initialize frappe bench (python 3.11, frappe branch version-15)\n3. setup config\n4. run bench new-site sitename\n5. It will start fine, but fails after ~ 85% with this error:\n```\nImportError: Module import failed for Dropbox Settings, the DocType you're trying to open might be deleted.\nError: No module named 'pkg_resources' \n```\n\n**Expected behavior** :chart_with_upwards_trend:\nBench new-site should complete without issues (working fine with v16)\n\n**OS (please complete the following information):** :cyclone:\n- Latest docker bench image ([v5.29.0](https://hub.docker.com/layers/frappe/bench/v5.29.0/images/sha256-5d126d010a3e16fac9990fc7f4638186295f3b85dc0f99e7cea89e6ffa6cbc36))\n- Bench Branch: develop\n- Frappe Version: 15\n\n**Workaround**:\nRun `uv pip install --reinstall setuptools==81.0.0` before creating a new site.\n\n**Possible Solution** :bookmark_tabs:\nLock setuptools version to 81.0.0 for now and/or manually add `pkg_resources` as an additional ressource.\n", "hints_text": "https://github.com/frappe/frappe/issues/36905\n\n", "all_hints_text": "https://github.com/frappe/frappe/issues/36905\nI think we should just downgrade the package to 81 as it is the recommended way described in https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/530d11498af526c4210d8eeaa1ed6c63f44a390f\n\n> ``pkg_resources`` has been removed from Setuptools. Most common uses of ``pkg_resources`` have been superseded by the `importlib.resources <https://docs.python.org/3/library/importlib.resources.html>`_ and `importlib.metadata <https://docs.python.org/3/library/importlib.metadata.html>`_ projects. Projects and environments relying on ``pkg_resources`` for namespace packages or other behavior should depend on older versions of ``setuptools``.\n\n\nThere is now a fix on the branch version-15-hotfix (not yet merged into version-15):\n\nhttps://github.com/frappe/frappe/commit/6272505652c5f43c66e91e0ab1f63dca2853e537\n\nHowever, the linked Bench PR (https://github.com/frappe/bench/pull/1699\nis critical. Without it, every Frappe v15 user is forced to upgrade Frappe and ERPNext, which is not feasible for many.\n\n:tada: This issue has been resolved in version 5.29.1 :tada:\n\nThe release is available on:\n- [GitHub release](https://github.com/frappe/bench/releases/tag/v5.29.1)\n- `v5.29.1`\n\nYour **[semantic-release](https://github.com/semantic-release/semantic-release)** bot :package::rocket:\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/frappe/bench/commit/f7fe2369d4c765850fca659b76bdebd38cb282bc"], "created_at": "2026-02-09T14:18:21Z"}
